SIMPLE: groundling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Groundling
<hw>Ground"ling</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Ground</ets> +
<ets>-ling</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A fish that
keeps at the bottom of the water, as the loach.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A spectator in the pit of a theater, which formerly
was on the ground, and without floor or benches.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No comic buffoon to make the <qex>groundlings</qex> laugh.</q>
<rj><qau>Coleridge.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Groundly</ent>⟦br⟧
